content: [Genenft #2: 2 Editions] - In the beginning... Just 379,000 years after the Big Bang, our Universe had cooled and expanded enough for light to finally pass through it. Since then light from that moment has been travelling through the cosmos for billions of years. Finally, it hits the sensors of the Plank satellite, creating a picture of the Universe in its youngest state. This dappled pattern is known as the Cosmic Microwave Background, one of the strongest pieces of evidence for our Universe's violent beginnings. This artistic impression of the first days of a young, molten Earth uses the Cosmic Microwave Background to pattern the mountains and lava lakes. The beginning of the Universe, in the beginning of Earth. Data sources - CMB: https://irsa.ipac.caltech.edu/data/Planck/release_1/all-sky-maps/previews/COM_CompMap_CMB-smica_2048_R1.20/index.html Starmap: https://svs.gsfc.nasa.gov/4851

content: [celestial body #1] - I wanted to understand more about visual communication with this series, to do so i engrossed myself in the style and meaning of others greater than myself. In the beginning we are beings of pure feeling. This is the kind of  interpretation of emotion Rothko tried to present in their work from my view. Through attempting that style with the added layer of braille to reinforce the feeling and disconnect from it I began to understand more about vocalising my own spectrum of emotions. The first 3 pieces are ones of hard contrast, built upon the same base braille texture re coloured in an effort to convey the 6 highs and lows of different feelings.But in truth they only convey 3 to me as the deepest negative of each feeling is all the same, a void. As i began to explore more I felt each piece become a truer representation of our emotional states, they shift, they arent equal, the split rise and fall in unexpected ways. They're open to interpretation.
